The goal in designing this quartet of pedestals was to make them as unique as possible. The CMTC team designed the pedestals to take advantage of additive manufacturing techniques, and incorporate features that are most readily manufactured with additive manufacturing. Furthermore, each pedestal’s design highly considers the display objects they hold on top and aim to compliment them. All the meanwhile, the pedestals aim to remain modular and easy to assemble!<br>

The static pedestal top includes recesses to store parts of a custom rod and node building system, while the surface is a building surface to anchor your creations! The dynamic pedestal top has five steps, each of which showcases a different application of additive manufacturing to moving parts. The recreational pedestal table has a chess board built in, and finally the artistic pedestal top enables viewing capabilities for the unique shadow orbs. <br>

