  From there, a grid of 49 design alternatives was then created which depicts every possible pedestal base and pedestal top combination. A conjoint analysis was performed to select what pedestal bases and what pedestal tops were most preferred by users.  Then several visual tests were done to help narrow down the design further.  These surveys tested user interest, user’s willingness to approach the pedestal, the pedestal’s cohesiveness with the kiosk experience, how futuristic the pedestal’s design was, and to what degree the pedestal was perceived to showcase the advantages of additive manufacturing. Feedback from surveys was incorporated into the final pedestal design.
